text: Edina Kotsis (born 27 June 1990) is a Hungarian taekwondo practitioner. She won a bronze medal in featherweight at the 2015 World Taekwondo Championships, after being defeated by Eva Calvo in the semifinal. Her achievements at the European Taekwondo Championships include a silver medal in 2012; she also participated in 2008, 2010, 2014, and 2018. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Hungarian female taekwondo practitioners Category:European Games competitors for Hungary Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2015 European Games Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:European Taekwondo Championships medalists
